{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Root cause:** The DSL parser stores prompt/script values in their raw syntax form, e.g. `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`. The `handleAPIStepContent` handler was using this raw value directly as a file path, so `os.ReadFile` was looking for a file literally named `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` — which doesn't exist.","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877810523Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877836231Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Fix (two parts):**","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877838996Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877844597Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **`handleAPIStepContent`** (`handler.go:1177`): Extract the actual path from `file(\"...\")` wrapper before reading the file, for both `prompt` and `script` config values.","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877846951Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877852542Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (`handler.go:1104`): Strip the `file(\"...\")` wrapper from config values sent to the frontend, so the drawer metadata shows clean paths like `.cloche/prompts/implement.md` instead of `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`.","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877854826Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T03:59:21.877857852Z"}
